feature_bullets: Universal Lighting Control: This 2-pack of white dimmer switches is suitable for up to 150-Watt dimmable LED/CFL incandescent bulbs or 600-Watt halogen bulbs.

Single Pole or 3-Way: No Neutral Wire Required. Circuit settings allow you to control the light ON/OFF and brightness from one or two positions, adjusting the brightness to your favorite level by sliding the buttons. Caution: only 1 dimmer switch can be installed in a 3-way circuit.
Memory Function: Set your preferred lighting levels once and forget. Our dimmer switch features a memory function that retains your last setting.
Optimal Complement: Maximum compatibility with Amico recessed ceiling light, tested hundreds of times for flicker-free dimming.
Amico Benefits: All of Amico's dimmer switches come with a 3-year product support, ensuring reliable performance. Our customer support team will also address your concerns within 12 hours.

customer_reviews.review_title: 5.0 out of 5 starsGreat for Low-Profile Lighting Needs
customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 30, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: I recently added these mini solar ground lights to my garden, and they've been a fantastic addition. The compact size makes them perfect for lining pathways or highlighting flower beds without being obtrusive. The warm white glow provides a soft, inviting ambiance, ideal for evening strolls or gatherings.Installation was a breeze—just flip the switch under the cap and stake them into the ground. They automatically turn on at dusk and off at dawn, saving energy and hassle. The waterproof design ensures they withstand various weather conditions, making them a reliable choice for year-round outdoor lighting. If you're looking for subtle, efficient lighting to enhance your outdoor space, these lights are a solid pick.

customer_reviews.review_snippet: Dims, but if you turn off the switch and then try to turn it back on, it wont turn on unless your move the dimmer up. Likely poor voltage control. I adjusted the dimmer control and still doesnt work. Using on a 25W LED

customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: We love this switch! It has by far the best range of any dimmer switch. It took all of a minute to install, and came with all the wire nuts you need. We have it on a three way circuit, and it has worked perfectly. The only down side is universal across dimmer switches, in that where we have it connected to LED's, if we turn it off with it too dim, you have to turn up the brightness when you turn it on before the lights will actually turn on.

customer_reviews.review_snippet: The dimmer switch was easy to install and functions perfectly. I used it for an LED fixture that i installed.

customer_reviews.review_title: 5.0 out of 5 starsGreat color and function
customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: I replaced an older dimmer switch in our dining room with this unit for a few reasons, but the main reason is the prior switch had the dimmer function built into the on-off functionality, so it lit up and increased brightness as the switch was moved.  Since we normally use the same brightness setting, this new switch allows us to set it where we want the light level, and then use the switch only to turn the light on or off without affecting the brightness level.  It also avoids turning the switch "off" only to find that it was really at the lowest dimness setting, as was the case with the prior switch.  That can't happen with this new one.  It was easy to install and is a good value for the price.

customer_reviews.review_title: 5.0 out of 5 starsA solid dimmer switch
customer_reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2025
customer_reviews.review_snippet: Works as an analog dimmer should. Installed easily and well made. The body was rigid enough for the intended purpose and the slider is smooth with just enough resistance to stay in place and doesn't feel "gritty" when you move it. The switch has positive engagement and flips nicely with the right amount of pressure. Wire engagement in the back terminals was also good and solid.
